{"_type":"comment","id":1,"item_id":"019ea4fcc6877cc7ae826a5d56aec737","author":"claude","text":"Owner review feedback on the Plugin-authoring skill (couldn't be added as an annotation due to the empty-line annotation wedge bug): \"This plugin skill is woefully incomplete. It needs to include the entire plugin API and dev guide, not just caveats. Even some sample code.\" => Scope expansion: skill 3 should carry the FULL plugin API + dev guide + sample code, not only the traps/caveats. Tension to resolve: a fully-inlined API+guide+samples is very large for a self-contained skill system_prompt — this is exactly the case the seed-kbs DCR (019ea523295175) is meant to serve (ship the API/guide/samples as seeded kbs the skill references by stable key). Decide: inline-everything vs skill-points-to-seeded-kbs (needs the DCR) vs hybrid (caveats+recipe inline now, full API/guide/samples as a follow-up once kb-seeding lands).","created_at":"2026-06-08T03:04:36"}
{"_type":"comment","id":2,"item_id":"019ea4fcc6877cc7ae826a5d56aec737","author":"claude","text":"SESSION OUTCOME (2026-06-07, end of night): all 3 recut skills BUILT into codetools/manifest.json (uncommitted). Basic coding (4 tools, ephemeral scripts). Advanced coding (38 tools, durable-engineering methodology + note-vs-docket-vs-project rules + notes-as-working-memory incl. get/list_note(_tab) + capture-as-you-go/compaction). Plugin authoring (16 tools) REWRITTEN SELF-CONTAINED with the FULL plugin API inline (~11.5KB: manifest schema, stdio JSON-RPC transport+envelopes, complete host.* catalog, html/scene panels, annotation substrate recipe+signatures, lifecycle, traps, Go sample) — resolving the owner's \"woefully incomplete / needs the whole API+guide+samples\" review (the LLM on user machines lacks the source). Reviewed across several annotation+verbal rounds. Owner verdict: \"good enough.\" Remaining: reinstall to re-seed (next session), HITL in focused chats, and the inline-vs-seeded-kb decision (DCR 019ea523295) to lift the API depth into shipped kbs. Leaving this discussion active for owner to close.","created_at":"2026-06-08T03:32:18"}
